        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 5:22PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southwest of Fowler, or 26 miles southeast of Pueblo Airport,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail could accumulate on roadways making driving
hazardous.

Locations impacted include...
Fowler.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
